name: Liverpool
summary: Liverpool's Premier League title hopes have suffered a setback after a 2-0 loss to Everton, who recorded a crucial win in the Merseyside derby. The Reds' struggles were highlighted by poor performances from key players like Virgil van Dijk and Alisson, who both received low ratings of 5/10. Despite a 3-1 victory over Fulham, Liverpool's title aspirations have been further damaged by a 2-2 draw against West Ham United. Off the pitch, rumors are circulating that Feyenoord manager Arne Slot has agreed to a contract to replace Jurgen Klopp as Liverpool's manager. The team's struggles have been evident in recent matches, with tensions between Mohamed Salah and Klopp reportedly reaching a boiling point.
